<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The local pointer 'impl' is declared as OS_impl_file_internal_record_t *impl (pointer to non-const). In OS_GenericSeek_Impl it is only used for read-only access (impl->fd is read to call lseek), so the pointer should be to a const-qualified type (const OS_impl_file_internal_record_t *impl). Therefore this code violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13. (Assigning the address of the global non-const table element to a const pointer is allowed; change the declaration to const OS_impl_file_internal_record_t *impl.)
</scenario>
